The paper deals with the problem of binary jumbled pattern matching, which involves string algorithms and data structures. The paper presents new results for this problem, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-categories.
